quran[9]{c,v,t,f}:
30,16,"As for those who disbelieved {1} and gave the lie to Our Signs and to the encounter of the Hereafter, they will be arraigned for chastisement.",footnotes:1:One thing here is noteworthy. Good works have been mentioned as a necessary adjunct of the faith
30,17,"So {1} glorify Allah {2} in the evening and the morning.",footnotes:1:“So”
30,18,"His is all praise in the heavens and in the earth; (and glorify Him) in the afternoon and when the sun begins to decline. {1}",footnotes:1:This verse clearly points to the times of the Fajr (morning)
30,19,"He brings forth the living from the dead and brings forth the dead from the living, and revives the earth after it is dead. {1} Likewise will you be raised to life (after you die).",footnotes:1:That is
30,20,"And of His {1} Signs is that He created you from dust and behold, you became human beings, and are multiplying around (the earth). {2}",footnotes:1:It should be noted that from here to the end of (verse 27)
30,21,"And of His Signs is that He has created mates for you from your own kind {1} that you may find peace in them {2} and He has set between you love and mercy. {3} Surely there are Signs in this for those who reflect.",footnotes:1:That is
30,22,"And of His Signs is the creation of the heavens and the earth {1} and the diversity of your tongues and colours. {2} Indeed there are Signs in this for the wise.",footnotes:1:That is
30,23,"And of His Signs is your sleeping at night and your seeking His Bounty {1} during the day. Indeed there are Signs in this for those who hearken.",footnotes:1:“To seek bounty” is to seek the livelihood. Though man generally sleeps at night and works for his living in the day
30,24,"And of His Signs is that He shows you lightning, arousing both fear and hope, {1} and sends down water from the sky and revives the earth after it is dead. {2} Indeed there are Signs in this for those who use their reason.",footnotes:1:That is
